qas.question: DeveloperWorks has content about open industry standard technologies like Java and SOA, what is one other industry standard technology it has resources for?

qas.question: What Java products are a part of the Ajax site?

context: <a0_0><b6_0>DeveloperWorks<b6_0/><a0_0/> is a website run by IBM for software developers and IT professionals. It contains how-to articles and tutorials, as well as software downloads and code samples, discussion forums, podcasts, blogs, wikis, and other resources for developers and technical professionals. Subjects range from open, industry-standard technologies like <b9_0>Java, <a2_0>Linux<a2_0/>, SOA<b9_0/> and web services, web development, Ajax, PHP, and XML to IBM's products (<b7_0>WebSphere, Rational, <a3_0>Lotus, Tivoli and Information Management<b7_0/><a3_0/>). In <a4_0><b8_0>2007<b8_0/><a4_0/>, developerWorks <a1_0>was inducted into <b5_0>the Jolt Hall of Fame<b5_0/><a1_0/>.
